The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graph classes, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of approximation algorithms and fixed-parameter algorithms also points towards cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper discusses kernelization complexity, which is a topic often studied in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
